30#ifndef _AVL
31#define _AVL
32
33#include <ldap_cdefs.h>
34
35/*
36 * this structure represents a generic avl tree node.
37 */
38
39LDAP_BEGIN_DECL
40
41typedef struct avlnode Avlnode;
42
43struct avlnode {
44 void* avl_data;
45 struct avlnode *avl_link[2];
46 char avl_bits[2];
47 signed char avl_bf;
48};
49
50#define avl_left avl_link[0]
51#define avl_right avl_link[1]
52#define avl_lbit avl_bits[0]
53#define avl_rbit avl_bits[1]
54
55#ifdef AVL_INTERNAL
56
57#define NULLAVL ((Avlnode *) NULL)
58
59/* balance factor values */
60#define LH (-1)
61#define EH 0
62#define RH 1
63
64#define avl_bf2str(bf) ((bf) == -1 ? "LH" : (bf) == 0 ? "EH" : (bf) == 1 ? "RH" : "(unknown)" )
65
66/* thread bits */
67#define AVL_THREAD 0
68#define AVL_CHILD 1
69
70/* avl routines */
71#define avl_getone(x) ((x) == 0 ? 0 : (x)->avl_data)
72#define avl_onenode(x) ((x) == 0 || ((x)->avl_left == 0 && (x)->avl_right == 0))
73
74#endif /* AVL_INTERNALS */
75
76#define avl_child(x,dir) ((x)->avl_bits[dir]) == AVL_CHILD ? \
77 (x)->avl_link[dir] : NULL
78#define avl_lchild(x) avl_child(x,0)
79#define avl_rchild(x) avl_child(x,1)
80
81typedef int (*AVL_APPLY) LDAP_P((void *, void*));
82typedef int (*AVL_CMP) LDAP_P((const void*, const void*));
83typedef int (*AVL_DUP) LDAP_P((void*, void*));
84typedef void (*AVL_FREE) LDAP_P((void*));
85
86LDAP_AVL_F( int )
87avl_free LDAP_P(( Avlnode *root, AVL_FREE dfree ));
88
89LDAP_AVL_F( int )
90avl_insert LDAP_P((Avlnode **, void*, AVL_CMP, AVL_DUP));
91
92LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
93avl_delete LDAP_P((Avlnode **, void*, AVL_CMP));
94
95LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
96avl_find LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP));
97
98LDAP_AVL_F( Avlnode* )
99avl_find2 LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP));
100
101LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
102avl_find_lin LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP));
103
104#ifdef AVL_NONREENTRANT
105LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
106avl_getfirst LDAP_P((Avlnode *));
107
108LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
109avl_getnext LDAP_P((void));
110#endif
111
112LDAP_AVL_F( int )
113avl_dup_error LDAP_P((void*, void*));
114
115LDAP_AVL_F( int )
116avl_dup_ok LDAP_P((void*, void*));
117
118LDAP_AVL_F( int )
119avl_apply LDAP_P((Avlnode *, AVL_APPLY, void*, int, int));
120
121LDAP_AVL_F( int )
122avl_prefixapply LDAP_P((Avlnode *, void*, AVL_CMP, void*, AVL_CMP, void*, int));
123
124LDAP_AVL_F( int )
125tavl_free LDAP_P(( Avlnode *root, AVL_FREE dfree ));
126
127LDAP_AVL_F( int )
128tavl_insert LDAP_P((Avlnode **, void*, AVL_CMP, AVL_DUP));
129
130LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
131tavl_delete LDAP_P((Avlnode **, void*, AVL_CMP));
132
133LDAP_AVL_F( void* )
134tavl_find LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP));
135
136LDAP_AVL_F( Avlnode* )
137tavl_find2 LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP));
138
139LDAP_AVL_F( Avlnode* )
140tavl_find3 LDAP_P((Avlnode *, const void*, AVL_CMP, int *ret));
141
142#define TAVL_DIR_LEFT 0
143#define TAVL_DIR_RIGHT 1
144
145LDAP_AVL_F( Avlnode* )
146tavl_end LDAP_P((Avlnode *, int direction ));
147
148LDAP_AVL_F( Avlnode* )
149tavl_next LDAP_P((Avlnode *, int direction ));
150
151/* apply traversal types */
152#define AVL_PREORDER 1
153#define AVL_INORDER 2
154#define AVL_POSTORDER 3
155/* what apply returns if it ran out of nodes */
156#define AVL_NOMORE (-6)
157
158LDAP_END_DECL
159
160#endif /* _AVL */
